In this speech at Mt. Olive Baptist Church in Buffalo, New York, the Vice President expresses his condolences to the Whitfield family and the other families affected by violence and hate. He discusses the epidemic of hate that the nation is currently facing and emphasizes the importance of strength, not in bringing others down, but in lifting others up. He calls on all good and God-loving people to stand up against hate and unite together. The Vice President also mentions the various acts of violence that have occurred in different places and emphasizes the need for solidarity and the protection of those who deserve it. He concludes by stating that no one should have to fight alone and that the strength of the people is greater than that of those motivated by hate.